HONEST REVIEW: Make sure you call ahead. I live around the corner and go here all the time. The food is good, chicken sandwich is fire (get it 9/10times) and can’t be beat for 6.99 with curly fries if you want poke go to coco cove. Grocery store is a bit pricy but that’s Waikiki for you. The main issue is the wait time. If you do the to go order you will have to wait in line for 20+ min, if you call ahead give yourself at least 5-10min to get through the line because they will keep your order at the register to pay and it gets busy during peak. Also they don’t always answer their phones which is annoying. I’ve called in store, heard it ring and the lady just ignored it. I asked her about it when I got to the register and she acted like she didn’t hear it so I called in front of her and the phone rang right behind her. Little bit of a D move but totally worth the awkward look on her face.  Summary: food 8/10 Service 5/10 Wait 5/10 Price 6/10 (depending on order) Overall 6/10
